The paper deals with the problem of partitioning the vertices of a unit disk graph into cliques, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of polynomial time approximation schemes (PTAS) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses a weighted version of the problem, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
